The bin packing problem is about packing items into bins of fixed size (here, bins are represented as an array where each element is the remaining capacity of the bin), and the goal is to minimize the number of bins used.

A heuristic is a strategy that makes choices at each step based on the current state, without necessarily considering all possibilities.

So, for the bin packing problem, a heuristic would select the next bin for the item based on some priority.

The priority function takes an item size and an array of bins (each element is the remaining capacity), and returns an array of priority scores for each bin.

The priority is used to select the best bin for the item.

