### Bin Packing Problem:
The bin packing problem is a well-known problem in computer science. Given a set of items of different sizes, the goal is to pack these items into the minimum number of bins of fixed capacity. In this case, the bins are of fixed size, and each item has a size less than or equal to the bin size.

The heuristic function `priority` assigns a priority score to each bin, which is used in the bin-packing algorithm to decide which bin to place the next item.

